| LG.Philips Develops World's First Color E-Paper                    |
|   from the i'd-love-me-some-of-that dept.                          |
|   posted by Zonk on Monday May 14, @00:34 (Displays)               |
|   http://hardware.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/14/0410247     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "LG.Philips LCD has announced it has developed
the [0]world's first 14.1-inch flexible color E-paper display, equivalent
in size to an A4 sheet of paper. The 14.1-inch flexible color E-paper
uses electronic ink from E-Ink Corp. to produce a maximum of 4,096
colors. It can be viewed from a full 180 degrees, so that images always
appear crisp, even when the display is bent."

