| Japanese Government to Move to OSS                                 |
|   from the a-little-less-time-on-hold dept.                        |
|   posted by Zonk on Monday May 14, @04:31 (Software)               |
|   http://linux.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/14/065239         |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "Linuxworld has up an article on the Japanese
government's plan to [0]reduce its reliance on a single IT vendor by
moving to open source software. 'Oracle, NEC, IBM, HP, Hitachi and Dell
are among 10 IT equipment and software vendors that are forming a
consortium to develop and sell Linux-based servers and computers for the
Japanese market. The move by the vendors to collaborate on Linux in Japan
comes from a edict from the country's government to make Linux and open
source a priority for all IT procurements, starting this July.' The
government has said explicitly it wants to decrease its reliance on
Microsoft as a server operating system platform."

Discuss this story at:
    http://linux.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/05/14/065239

